    "description": "Focus Systems Corporation provides IT services for public and private clients in Japan. It operates through Public Related Business, Enterprise Business, Wide Area Solutions Business, and Innovative Business segments. The company also engages in the service of information security products; investment, development, and acting as intermediaries for companies and venture businesses; consulting and contract computer system development; systems operation and maintenance; development and distribution of information security technology and associated products, as well as software packages; planning and production of web content; temp staffing services; and other computer-related services. In addition, it is involved in the provision of technical support services for the realization of social infrastructure systems, such as my number-related, financial, trade, air traffic control, automobile-related, and insurance and pension systems; development of communication control systems, software for information and communication devices, and embedded software; infrastructure design and construction, mainframe operations, and related services; and IoT and information products and solutions. Further, the company provides core system, computerization/efficiency, IT infrastructure, cloud/virtualization, security, and built-in technologies; and cryptography, digital watermark, beacon/directional receivers, and workflow/electronic contracts. It serves the communication, finance, social security, aviation, automobile/transportation, trade/transportation, electronic administration, and local government fields. Focus Systems Corporation was incorporated in 1977 and is headquartered in Shinagawa, Japan."
